OL,3,CBuilder who killed stranger in
OL,4,Cunprovoked one-punch attack jailed
OL,6,FHe pleaded guilty to the manslaughter
OL,7,Fof Mr Roberts and was jailed for six
OL,8,Fyears and eight months, with an
OL,9,Fextended licence period of two years.
OL,11,FJudge Catarina Sjolin Knight told him:
OL,12,F"I am sure you punched Mr Roberts once
OL,13,Fto the chin."
OL,15,FThe court heard Mr Roberts had spent a
OL,16,F"quiet evening" drinking with friends
OL,17,Fat the Queen in the West pub and was
OL,18,Fwalking home when he was attacked.
